The '''Caarites''' were a [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] porcine [[Species/Legends|species]] indigenous to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Caarimon]].

==Biology and appearance==
The species typically displayed broad grins, bearing a double row of flat, wide, and perfectly white teeth.<ref name="LFC">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref> Because of their native habitat, the species was well-suited for surviving in hot climates. Since extreme cold was unknown to this species, their ability to survive in such environments was hindered more than most species.

==Society and culture==
They were typically sly, ingratiating beings with an eye for profit. Their penchant for crooked business dealings was regularly cloaked by their friendly demeanor. This caused them to suffer from a poor reputation, though, making outsider trust of the species rare. When dealing with large groups of individuals directly, their charm was often described as "childlike," exemplifying their guise of innocence. They were often described as "friendly, entertaining, and humorous."<ref name="LFC" />

Every Caarite knew the native [[Caarimala]] language, [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Galactic Basic Standard]], and at least one other language. Communication was considered a fundamental skill for their society. This was especially true as the species favored nonviolent means of dealing with an adversary in a face-to-face encounter. Caarites were occasionally [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]], though their inherent greed prevented them from truly embracing the ways of the Jedi.<ref name="LFC" />

==History==
The Caarites were members of the [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]]. When the Federation [[Invasion of Naboo/Legends|blockaded Naboo]], the Caarites were convinced it would cause the end of the Federation, so convinced the [[Filordus|Filordi]] to split off with them in forming the [[Metatheran Cartel]]. Of the two member species of the Cartel, the Caarites served as the public face.<ref name="LFC" />

As the Caarites were well-known in the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]], the alien ever-smiling crew of the local [[Dorumaa Resort]] were jokingly known as "Neo-Caarites," even though they were [[Gungan/Legends|Gungans]], [[Human/Legends|Humans]] and [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'leks]].<ref name="LFC" />

